args:
While waiting for Gatov, the party seeks
to help out in the slums. The residents are
suspicious at first, but after saving a child and
helping at a clinic, they are thanked. However,
the prince learns from the experience that
fleeting good deeds are not always welcome.
What is it, Elisanne? You appear to be\nquite deep in thought.
Looking over the state of this place,\nI cannot help but to feel conflicted.
You can say that again. The main street is\nfancier than my best hat, but this place is\nsadder than Ranzal's old boot.
If we take the main street to be the light\nof Grams, this area is its shadow—and\nan area that has been wholly forsaken.
Hey, guys? I have an idea.
Until Gatov comes back, we should go\naround and see if there's anything we can\ndo to help the people in this district.
Hey, yeah! That'll be a great way to thank\n'em for hiding us and all that!
I'm all about helping folks. Let's do it!
It's a wonderful idea, though I question\nwhether there is anything we can do...
Well, we won't know until we try,\nso let's get out there and find some\nfolks in need!
Excuse me, what are you doing?
Home repair. What's it to you—and why\nthe hell is somebody dressed as fancy\nas you down here in the slums anyway?
Oh, I'm not from Grams.\nI'm just a traveler.
I was wondering if there was a way I could\nhelp out while I'm staying here.
You were ＂wondering＂? The hell you say!\nGet outta here before you hurt yourself.
Heeeey, guys! What's the haps?\nWhatcha doin'? Can I help?
I'm Luca. I'm from South Grast—
Those kids just ran away from me...\nME! Adorable ol' Luca!
Cleo and I struck out as well, I'm afraid.
The people here are all very much on their\nguard and not especially forthcoming.
It's like everybody here is totally\nsuspicious of us or something.
Thus is the world of the slums: If a random\nstranger arrives suddenly to offer aid,\npeople can't help but doubt their motives.
No matter how we might like to help,\nwe shall accomplish nothing until we\ncan gain the trust of the citizens here.
Sorry, everyone. Seems like\nI was being a little naive.
Well? What do we do now,\n{player_name}?
There must be SOMEONE here who needs\nour help and is willing to take it.\nWe should ask around a little more.
By Ilia! What was that sound?!
It came from that house that was being\nrepaired! Come on, everyone!
Are you okay?! Come on, stay with me!\nI'm gonna move this stuff right away!\nDammit... Somebody, somebody HELP!
A boy is caught beneath those building\nmaterials! We have to help him!
You're the guy from earlier... But fine!\nYou wanna help, here's your chance!
Let's lift this stuff on three. Ready?\nOne...two...THREE!
He's badly hurt. I'll heal him at once.
Yes, because I healed you with magic.
Oh, sweet mercy... Okay now, lad.\nThis place is dangerous, understand?\nDon't let me see you 'round here anymore.

Thanks, friends. Oh, and sorry about
earlier—I figured you were here to rub
your big-city looks in our faces. Guess you
really shouldn't judge a book by its cover.

Please don't apologize. I just showed up
and started talking to you without
understanding your situation, so it's
no wonder you were suspicious.

I just wanted to find a way to show my
thanks for everyone hiding us while we
wait for Gatov, but I ended up needlessly
putting you on your guard instead.
Huh? You're guests of Gatov's?\nWell, why didn't you say so sooner?
Nobody around here who doesn't, honestly.\nYeah, this all makes sense now.
Actually, there's a medical clinic nearby.\nYou mind going there and helping their\npatients the way you just did here?
There. You should be all right now.
The pain, it's...gone.\nThank you so much!
You're quite welcome. Please take good\ncare of yourself, all right?
Whew! I think that was the last of them.
Good work, you two! Zena and Cleo\nare bona fide heroines!
I can't tell you how much help you all\nhave been—and you were so quick, too!
Things certainly would be different if we\nhad you folks around here all the time!
Ha ha! Hey, don't worry about it—we're\nnot in the habit of kidnapping travelers\nand forcing them to work in clinics.
But if you DO happen to be in Grams in\nthe future, we'd appreciate any help\nyou're willing to give us.
We'll do what we can. I promise.
Looks like we were able to be of some use.
Yes, though we were only able to help\na scant few people in the end.
Yes, it is a shame we did so little\nwhen so many in this district suffer.

True, but showing up and trying to foist
help on people only ends up making its
own kind of trouble. That's a lesson I
learned today that I won't soon forget.
If you want to help someone, it's essential\nto first take the time to talk to them and\nearn their trust through your actions.
And I'm sure that Gatov has made that\nkind of effort. He's an amazing person.
But why does the Church of Grams do\nnothing? Can they truly be intentionally\nignoring the plight of this district?
Yes, it seems there's a complex situation\nin Grams that we've still yet to uncover.
